## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Do you want the FVD/SVD computed in the wavenumber (FFT) domain or using spatial finite differences?**
> - **FFT domain** (recommended): more accurate for potential field data, handles edge effects via padding. Requires no extra dependencies beyond `numpy`.
> - **Finite differences**: simpler, faster for quick QC, slightly less accurate.
> The plan above uses **FFT** for vertical derivatives and **`np.gradient`** for horizontal derivatives — this is the standard approach.

> [!NOTE]
> **Should the derivatives also be clipped to the BMC bounding box** before saving, or keep the full extent of the source grid? 
> Current plan: keep full extent (same footprint as the reprojected source TIF).

> [!NOTE]
> **Should we add a quick matplotlib visualization** (PNG export) of each derivative for QC purposes?
> This would allow you to visually inspect each grid right after running the script.

